{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17509219","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17509219"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:15:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:15:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11405"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11405","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11405"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.28,0.39,0.13,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4041"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"54341"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4041","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4041"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11405"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"39849"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1482"},{"type":"tags","id":"2100"},{"type":"tags","id":"2664"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11627"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"4636"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6319"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15491"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42591"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44699"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"54341","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/54341"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 58-year-old man has presented to clinic for a pre-anaesthetic assessment. He is booked for an elective open right-sided inguinal hernia repair. His medical history is unremarkable aside from a \u0027valve problem\u0027 diagnosed during childhood, the details of which is he unable to recall. He denies chest pain, shortness of breath, palpitations or ankle swelling and is able to climb two flights of stairs with no difficulty. Auscultation of the praecordium reveals a widely split S2 and systolic ejection murmur heard maximally at the upper left sternal border.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which of the following manoeuvres is most likely to increase the intensity of this murmur?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Left lateral decubitus position","Leaning forward, full expiration","Full inspiration","Full expiration","Valsalva maneovure"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFull inspiration\u003C/strong\u003E \u2013 The presence of a systolic ejection murmur heard maximally at the upper left sternal border in combination with a widely split S2 is consistent with pulmonary stenosis. Stenosis of the pulmonary valve is a relatively common congenital defect often remaining asymptomatic during childhood. However, with age the valve may undergo fibrous thickening, which may lead to increased outlet obstruction and development of symptoms. The splitting of the second heart sound is due to a prolonged ejection phase through the stenosed pulmonary valve and thus a delay in closure.\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003EFull inspiration during auscultation is a useful manoeuvre in distinguishing left and right-sided heart murmurs (e.g. aortic stenosis vs. pulmonary stenosis and tricuspid regurgitation vs. mitral regurgitation). \u2022 Full inspiration increases the intensity of all right-sided murmurs due to an increase in venous return to the right ventricle (but reduces the intensity of left-sided murmurs due to decreased venous return to the left ventricle) \u2022 In contrast, full expiration increases the intensity of all left-sided murmurs\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003ELeft lateral decubitus position \u2013 This manoeuvre increases the murmur of mitral stenosis, which is typically a mid-diastolic murmur.\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003ELeaning forward, full expiration \u2013 This manoeuvre increases the murmur of aortic regurgitation, which, is typically an early diastolic murmur heard maximally over Erb\u2019s point.\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003EFull expiration \u2013 This manoeuvre increases the intensity of left-sided murmurs and decreases the intensity of right-sided murmurs.\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003EValsalva maneovure \u2013 This manoeuvre increases the intensity of the murmur heard in HOCM.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The murmur of pulmonary stenosis is best heard during full inspiration."],"references":["Cuypers JA, Witsenburg M, van der Linde D, et al. Pulmonary stenosis: update on diagnosis and therapeutic options. Heart. 2013 Mar; 99:339-47."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"39849"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11405"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"39849","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/39849"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-04T10:02:42+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-04T10:02:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4041"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"54341"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"1","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude34","name":"Anaesthesia","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"a